4. If the issue is a "Switching Loop," explain which protocol should have prevented
this and why it might have failed.
=> Switching Loop:
Spanning Tree Protocol (STP) should prevent loops by blocking redundant ports. It might have failed due to: STP disabled, BPDU Guard missing, or incompatible vendor implementations.

